<segment id="1" parent="1001" relname="preparation">Get Along With</segment>
<segment id="2" parent="1002" relname="preparation">Conceptual Thinkers</segment>
<segment id="3" parent="1003" relname="span">Ever dealt with someone</segment>
<segment id="4" parent="3" relname="elaboration">who cannot put anything in concrete terms ?</segment>
<segment id="5" parent="1006" relname="joint">Someone who speaks big words</segment>
<segment id="6" parent="1006" relname="joint">and has a broad image of how the world works ,</segment>
<segment id="7" parent="1007" relname="same_unit">but</segment>
<segment id="8" parent="9" relname="condition">whenever you try to get specifics out of them ,</segment>
<segment id="9" parent="1008" relname="span">it 's like herding cats ?</segment>
<segment id="10" parent="1011" relname="preparation">Steps</segment>
<segment id="11" parent="1012" relname="sequence">Take stock of the individual 's relevance / importance for your everyday life .</segment>
<segment id="12" parent="1014" relname="span">The more important the person is</segment>
<segment id="13" parent="1015" relname="span">the more you should make an effort</segment>
<segment id="14" parent="1016" relname="span">to relate to them</segment>
<segment id="15" parent="14" relname="elaboration">( and them to you ) .</segment>
<segment id="16" parent="1017" relname="span">Explain things on their terms .</segment>
<segment id="17" parent="1018" relname="sequence">For example , is it important to convey to your dad what your college major classes are about ?</segment>
<segment id="18" parent="1020" relname="condition">If this matters to you</segment>
<segment id="19" parent="1020" relname="span">think about " transferable skills " and important lessons</segment>
<segment id="20" parent="1021" relname="span">you learn</segment>
<segment id="21" parent="1022" relname="span">-</segment>
<segment id="22" parent="1023" relname="span">your dad may not care to know about the second derivative problem</segment>
<segment id="23" parent="1024" relname="span">you failed on the exam</segment>
<segment id="24" parent="23" relname="condition">if he 's a conceptual thinker and not a math-whiz .</segment>
<segment id="25" parent="1011" relname="joint">Do you need to explain to your roommate</segment>
<segment id="26" parent="1027" relname="question">why you need to be alone on Friday night in the apartment ?</segment>
<segment id="27" parent="1029" relname="span">If he or she is a conceptual thinker</segment>
<segment id="28" parent="1030" relname="span">they will be confused by all your literal</segment>
<segment id="29" parent="28" relname="elaboration">( and detailed )</segment>
<segment id="30" parent="1028" relname="span">Friday evening plans .</segment>
<segment id="31" parent="1032" relname="span">Hearing concepts such as " privacy " , " personal space " , " date " , " movie night " may be more important to them than the details of who your date is or what movie</segment>
<segment id="32" parent="31" relname="elaboration">you are planning to see .</segment>
<segment id="33" parent="1034" relname="condition">If you are planning to do something with them ,</segment>
<segment id="34" parent="1034" relname="joint">patiently and respectfully of your thinking styles</segment>
<segment id="35" parent="1036" relname="span">try to get them to commit to concrete steps or specifics</segment>
<segment id="36" parent="35" relname="elaboration">about what will you do .</segment>
<segment id="37" parent="1037" relname="sequence">For example ,</segment>
<segment id="38" parent="1039" relname="condition">if your friend talks about " big life change " plans ,</segment>
<segment id="39" parent="1039" relname="sequence">get her or him to commit to running once a week with you ,</segment>
<segment id="40" parent="1041" relname="contrast">start an online dating profile ,</segment>
<segment id="41" parent="1042" relname="sequence">or pick up the call</segment>
<segment id="42" parent="1042" relname="sequence">and inquire about open position about her or his dream job .</segment>
<segment id="43" parent="1044" relname="span">Conceptual thinkers sometimes have a hard time making their plans concrete</segment>
<segment id="44" parent="43" relname="cause">because they need to think about details .</segment>
<segment id="45" parent="1045" relname="span">Help them</segment>
<segment id="46" parent="45" relname="elaboration">( and they can help you think in conceptual terms about your business idea , or your career/ life plans ) .</segment>
<segment id="47" parent="1047" relname="preparation">Tips</segment>
<segment id="48" parent="1049" relname="contrast">Conceptual and literal thinkers may have a hard time getting along</segment>
<segment id="49" parent="1050" relname="same_unit">but , with the right communication skills and patience ,</segment>
<segment id="50" parent="1050" relname="same_unit">they can be wonderful life or work partners .</segment>
<segment id="51" parent="1053" relname="attribution">Think for example of CEO-COO teams :</segment>
<segment id="52" parent="1053" relname="span">the CEO is in change of vision , mission , inspiring people ;</segment>
<segment id="53" parent="52" relname="elaboration">the COO spends time on the nitty-gritty of everyday life .</segment>
<segment id="54" parent="1047" relname="joint">Both are important ,</segment>
<segment id="55" parent="1056" relname="span">and the two have to work together as a team :</segment>
<segment id="56" parent="1057" relname="joint">mission without good execution is bad ,</segment>
<segment id="57" parent="1057" relname="joint">and so is execution without good , clear mission .</segment>
<segment id="58" parent="1047" relname="joint">Check out How to Get Along With Literal Thinkers .</segment>
<segment id="59" parent="1059" relname="span">You may be one of them</segment>
<segment id="60" parent="1060" relname="span">in</segment>
<segment id="61" parent="60" relname="elaboration">which case conceptual thinkers will make you very uncomfortable with their high-level ideas .</segment>
<segment id="62" parent="1061" relname="span">Warnings</segment>
<segment id="63" parent="1063" relname="span">Working with someone of an opposite thinking type can be both a blessing and a curse</segment>
<segment id="64" parent="63" relname="elaboration">( and sometimes both at the same time ) .</segment>
<segment id="65" parent="1062" relname="joint">Learn to recognize and use each other 's strengths .</segment>
